          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Fair Treatment of Scholarships Act of 2016 </b></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to modify the provision which excludes from the gross income of a student any amount that is received as a qualified scholarship used for qualified tuition and related expenses. </p> <p>The bill expands the exclusion to: (1) permit the scholarship to be used for room and board costs for which there is an allowance under the Higher Education Act of 1965; and (2) to specify that &quot;qualified tuition and related expenses&quot; include fees, books, supplies, and equipment required for research at the educational organization. </p> <p>The amount included in qualified tuition and related expenses for research not required for a course of instruction may not exceed $300 per year, adjusted for inflation after 2016. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2016-07-12T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
